// hve-squad OUTBOUND MCP server registration template (JSONC: JSON with comments)
//
// Purpose
//   Reference snippet for consumers who want to call the hve-squad as MCP
//   TOOLS from an MCP host (Phase 0: VS Code GitHub Copilot, over stdio).
//   This registers the squad's OWN server, which ships in the companion
//   repository Peter-N91/hve-squad-mcp (https://github.com/Peter-N91/hve-squad-mcp)
//   and exposes 5 coarse intent tools: squad_research, squad_plan,
//   squad_review, squad_architect, and squad_run.
//
//   This is the OUTBOUND inverse of the sibling `mcp.template.json`: that file
//   registers external servers the squad CONSUMES; this file registers the
//   squad server other hosts consume.
//
// Scope
//   This file is documentation only. The hve-squad APM package never reads or
//   writes the consumer's `.vscode/mcp.json`. You own the merge and override
//   of every entry below.
//
// How to use
//   1. Clone + build the server once (see the hve-squad-mcp README):
//        git clone https://github.com/Peter-N91/hve-squad-mcp
//        cd hve-squad-mcp && npm install && npm run build
//   2. Open or create `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace.
//   3. Copy the `servers` entry below into your file (merge with any servers
//      you already have; do not replace entries you depend on).
//   4. Pick the command form that matches your install (see the two options
//      in the entry) and delete the other.
//   5. Reload VS Code so Copilot picks up the new server, then ask Copilot to
//      "research X with the squad" — the squad_* tools become model-invocable.
//
// Execution model (Phase 0)
//   DELEGATED. Each tool returns the Squad Coordinator persona, the matched
//   routing row, and a framed dispatch request; VS Code's own agent host runs
//   the runSubagent/task loop to dispatch the cast. The server calls no model
//   and needs no credentials. The cloud surfaces (Copilot Studio, M365,
//   Cowork) arrive in Phase 1 over remote Streamable HTTP + Entra auth.
//
// Credentials
//   None. stdio inherits the local user's trust; no token, secret, or API key
//   is stored in this file.
{
  "servers": {
    "hve-squad": {
      // Phase 0: local stdio. The server runs as a child process of VS Code.
      "type": "stdio",

      // Option A (published package): run via npx. Use this once the
      // `squad-mcp` package is published to a registry your `npx` can reach.
      "command": "npx",
      "args": [
        "-y",
        "@hve-squad/mcp"
      ]

      // Option B (local build, not published): run the compiled entrypoint
      // directly. Replace Option A above with the two lines below, pointing
      // `args` at YOUR absolute path to the cloned hve-squad-mcp checkout's
      // dist/src/server.js:
      //   "command": "node",
      //   "args": ["/absolute/path/to/hve-squad-mcp/dist/src/server.js"]
    }
  }
}
